<dl id="n41050b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41050b">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41050b"> 50(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> your otherwise / accurate / account</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Reports must needs be written at top speed, and with little or no time for supervision; the risks of libel are always to be reckoned with&mdash;yet even the well-known formula of speakers who would qualify their statements &ldquo;In <mark>your otherwise accurate report</mark>, etc.&rdquo; are few and far between. <small> J.B. Hall, <a name="HRRR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#HRRR"><cite title="source">Random Records of a Reporter</cite></a> (n.d.) &lsquo;The Press.&rsquo; 239</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c06173e" href="c06all.htm#c06173e">VI.C.06:173(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
